Egocentric distance vs relative depth encoding

Endpoints

Distribution of the endpoints averaged across all subjects. Data is split across relative depth (40 and 50 mm).

Filled circles: middle position during vertical grasp. Triangles, diamonds and open circles: thumb, index and middle positions during horizontal grasp.

## N = 2

Comparison between difference between endpoints of the vertical grasp (red) and FGA of the horizontal grasp (green).
